# Blade And BladeWindUI UX Standards

- Prefer BladeWindUI components before writing custom HTML structures.
- Build reusable Blade components/partials for repeated UI patterns.
- Keep Blade templates presentational; do not place business logic in views.
- Keep PHP conditionals in views minimal and readability-focused.
- Pass prepared data from controllers/services/view models instead of heavy inline conditionals.
- Use consistent component props, slots, and naming for predictable templates.
- Prefer named slots for clarity when composing Blade components.

## UX And Accessibility Guardrails

- Every input needs an associated label and clear validation error feedback.
- Include empty states, loading states, and success/failure messaging.
- Use semantic HTML structure around BladeWindUI components.
- Preserve keyboard accessibility and readable focus order.

## Do Not

- Do not duplicate long markup blocks across multiple views.
- Do not query the database from Blade templates.
- Do not hide authorization logic in view-only checks when policy checks are required upstream.
